<collectingCountry box="[1000,1110,695,719]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Colombia</collectingCountry>
in which this subspecies is found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,495,766,791]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[501,764,767,791]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pygmalion" subSpecies="metaensis">
<emphasis box="[501,764,767,791]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. pygmalion metaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flies in open areas and grasslands in the vast savanna of the Orinoco basin (Rio Meta, Rio Ariari, Llanos Orientales) and along the eastern slope of the Cordillera Oriental in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,265,839,863]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. It is possible that 
<taxonomicName box="[493,764,839,863]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pygmalion" subSpecies="metaensis">
<emphasis box="[493,764,839,863]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. pygmalion metaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may occur in the state of Apure in 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1314,839,863]" name="Venezuela" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, down the Orinoco river since both countries share the same savanna ecosystem (Llanos Orientales) but no records available from 
<collectingCountry box="[213,328,911,935]" name="Venezuela" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
were found for this subspecies. 
<taxonomicName box="[693,958,911,935]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pygmalion" subSpecies="metaensis">
<emphasis box="[693,958,911,935]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. pygmalion metaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flies sympatrically with 
<taxonomicName box="[1239,1374,911,935]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Philaethria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="dido" subSpecies="dido">
<emphasis box="[1239,1374,911,935]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. dido dido</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in E. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,265,946,970]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,335,983,1007]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Host plant.</emphasis>
reared on 
<taxonomicName box="[472,667,983,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="edulis">
<emphasis box="[472,667,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Passiflora edulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[702,864,983,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Passifloraceae</taxonomicName>
) in E. 
<collectingCountry box="[956,1066,983,1007]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(Meta) (Gregory Nielsen pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,1074]" box="[197,1073,1049,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,403,1050,1074]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Immature stages.</emphasis>
fifith instar larva (
